          "date": "2018-02-23 18:00:55.000000000",
          "tz": 180
        },
        "subject": "LU-10628 tests: obdfilter-survey case=network fail",
        "message": "LU-10628 tests: obdfilter-survey case=network fail\n\nobdfilter-survey case=network always exits with non zero\nexit status in case of no client mounted because the statement\n   \"lctl dl| grep osc | grep -v mdt | grep UP\"\nreturns 1\n\nPatch turns off 'set -e' to correctly proceed the case of\nunmounted client.\n\nSigned-off-by: Alyona Romanenko <alyona.romanenko@seagate.com>\nSigned-off-by: Elena Gryaznova <c17455@cray.com>\nTest-Parameters: trivial testlist=obdfilter-survey osscount=1 ostcount=2 mdscount=1 mdtcount=1 clientcount=1\nCray-bug-id: MRP-2314\nReviewed-by: Andriy Skulysh <c17819@cray.com>\nReviewed-by: Elena Gryaznova <c17455@cray.com>\nChange-Id: Ie1b306f096bc267a4ea5e607b15de911a2ec8dda\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
